# Multi Chat Client

This project uses react, node.js, mongoDB, and Socket.io.
This also used Postman app to send dummy single via the program to store data on MongoDB
This also uses resend.com free plan to send emails. Because I do not wish to purchase a domain this will be used for testing purposes only and can only send emails to my email "michaelhullzero@gmail.com"
profile images stored in mongoDB will be gotten from Cloudinary.

The program also runs locally using a cloudflare Tunnel instead of port forwarding

To run the project open a command prompt terminal and run the command:

npm run start

if there are no node_modules files in the frontend or backend, or also not a dist file in the frontend run the command:

npm run build

if you want to run either the backend or the frontend run these commands:

cd frontend
npm run dev

cd backend
npm run dev

the.gitignore does not upload the .env variables
PORT=
MONGO_URL=
NODE_ENV=
JWT_SECRET=
RESEND_API_KEY = 
EMAIL_FROM =
EMAIL_FROM_NAME =
CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME =
CLOUDINARY_API_KEY =
CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET =

